news.title: Asking prices for UK houses stagnate in June: Rightmove
news.para: The company said the average asking price was 375,110 pounds ($475,827) for property put on sale between May 12 and June 8, down 21 pounds from a month earlier and statistically a flat reading.

news.title: China’s central bank keeps lending rate unchanged
news.para: The government reported Monday that factory output fell 5.6% in May from the year before, slowing from 6.7% in April, though analysts noted some impact due to more work days in this year compared with the year before.

news.title: New home prices in China fall 3.9% year-on-year in May 2024
news.para: Prices were down 0.7% in May from the previous month, marking the 11th straight month-on-month decline and steepest drop since October 2014, according to Reuters calculations based on National Bureau of Statistics (NBS) data.

news.title: Oyo in advance talks to raise Rs 1,000 crore
news.para: Oyo fundraise: Hospitality startup Oyo is raising around Rs 1,000 crore from family offices and investors. The fundraise aims to value Oyo at about $2.5 billion, marking a significant decrease from its peak valuation of $9 billion in 2021.

news.title: Delhi HC dismisses PIL seeking directions to raze alleged illegal construction
news.para: Keeping in view the fact that the present petition has been filed without adequate home work / investigation, this court dismisses the present public interest petition along with the application with costs of Rs 25,000 to be paid equally to the respondents

news.title: Complete projects under Dilli Gramodaya Abhiyan by August: Delhi LG
news.para: With 416 projects/works amounting to Rs 364.38 crore already being implemented under the ambitious Dilli Gramodaya Abhiyan, VK Saxena on Friday directed the agencies concerned to complete all awarded works by August this year.

news.title: Lucknow: Over 270 illegal buildings razed in Akbarnagar
news.para: In a rehabilitation effort, about 1,800 Pradhan Mantri A was Yojna (PMAY) houses were allotted to displaced families. In all, 14 excavators, 12 bulldozers and 15 water tankers with sprinklers have been used in carrying out the demolition drive.

news.title: Despite pushback, illegal buildings allowed to flourish in Bengaluru
news.para: The civic agency was supposed to take action and demolish these illegal structures within 117 days as per an order copy issued by the commissioner in July last year.

news.title: Goa: GIDC to hold fresh auction for commercial plots in Verna
news.para: The GIDC has also begun the process to issue the allotment letters for the 16 industrial plots that were auctioned in March.

news.title: Ambuja Cements may repay Penna's debt
news.para: With Adani's backing, lenders expect Penna to look to reduce cost and refinance or repay ₹6,600 crore term loans and ₹400 crore of high-cost debt from Edelweiss it took a few months ago.

news.title: Investors prefer single-owned and managed commercial properties
news.para: The rental yields for commercial assets across key property markets have been a major indicator that clearly shows that single-owned commercial properties are outperforming their strata counterparts that have multiple owners and operators.

news.title: Central Park plans to list real estate business in two-three years
news.para: The company has a launch pipeline of around ₹10,000 crore for FY25 and is in the process to appoint an audit firm. It is targeting ₹4,000 crore sales in FY25 and is likely to reach ₹10,000 crore sales by the time of listing.

news.title: Amaravati development works will be completed in 30 months: Andhra Pradesh minister
news.para: Narayana said the state capital of Amaravati will be developed as one of the top five capital cities in the world and that the plans devised in the past will be implemented to meet this target.

news.title: Adani Group only a project developer for Dharavi: Sources
news.para: The project aims to provide housing and commercial spaces, ensuring no displacement of Dharavi residents. Additional benefits include stamp duty exemptions and business support.

news.title: Delhi development body likely to start handing over EWS flats from July 2024
news.para: An official stated that out of the total 1,675 EWS flats constructed under “Jahan Jhuggi Wahin Makan” scheme, an in situ rehabilitation project, the allotment of 1,396 flats in Jailorwala Bagh was finalised in March.

news.title: Proposal to extend Delhi metro's red line approved
news.para: The Rithala-Narela-Kundli metro corridor will be constructed at a cost of Rs 6,231 crore with the Delhi portion estimated to cost Rs 5,685.22 crore and the Haryana portion Rs 545.77 crore, the statement said.

news.title: Greater Noida authority hikes land allocation rates by 5.30% in FY25
news.para: The finance department will soon issue an office order in this regard. The new rates will be considered effective from April 1," the GNIDA said, describing the 5.30 per cent rate hike as "modest

news.title: NCLT orders insolvency proceeding against Supertech Realtors
news.para: ​A two-member Delhi bench of NCLT admitted the insolvency plea filed by the Bank of Maharashtra over a default of Rs 168.04 crore and appointed Anju Agarwal as interim resolution professional (IRP), suspending the board of Supertech Realtors, a step-down subsidiary of Supertech.

news.title: Thane: Ex-official of bank among three booked for duping flat buyers of over Rs 4 crore
news.para: The accused were identified as Santosh Baburao Waghmare alias Tigerbhai, owner and partner of several construction firms, Vinayak Digambar Wakankar, former assistant general manager of the co-operative bank and Jagdish Bhale, the then senior clerk in the bank, he added.

news.title: Adani Electricity Mumbai begins power disconnection drive over non-payment of dues
news.para: In a statement, the Adani Group arm said over the years, residents were promised by prospective realty developers that their power bills will be taken care of, due to which they stopped payment.
